\begin_layout Standard
If we do not assume that the plasma is quasineutral, we have to solve Poisson's
 equation to get 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\nabla^{2}\phi=\nabla_{\|}^{2}\phi=\frac{e\left(n_{i}-n_{e}\right)}{\epsilon_{0}}.
\]

\end_inset

Normalising this
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\frac{T_{ref}}{e\lambda_{ref}^{2}}\hat{\nabla}^{2}\hat{\phi} & =\frac{en_{ref}}{\epsilon_{0}}\left(\hat{n}_{i}-\hat{n}_{e}\right)\\
\hat{\nabla}^{2}\hat{\phi} & =\frac{e^{2}n_{ref}\lambda_{ref}^{2}}{\epsilon_{0}T_{ref}}\left(\hat{n}_{i}-\hat{n}_{e}\right)
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\frac{e^{2}n_{ref}\lambda_{ref}^{2}}{\epsilon_{0}T_{ref}}$
\end_inset

 is a very large number.
 For 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{ref}=10^{19}m^{-3}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{ref}=0.1m$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{ref}=10eV$
\end_inset

